<Content>Four stars from this reviewer, 2nd business trip to this hotel I was here on business. This is my second business trip at the hotel. The service at the front desk, spa, gym, restaurants, concierge....all the service people were excellent.I drove over from the west coast of Florida where I reside. The only parking at the hotel is valet which is $30.00 per day which I thought was too high. I didn't care for the food at the hotel which was also too expensive. Keep in mind my tastes are not that sophisticated, so others may like eel, and other things that I have not eaten before. I liked the gym, the treadmills and stationary bikes each had individual television sets with headphones. There were different newspapers at the gym. There is an attendant in the gym who is very helpful. The sauna and steam room and shower facility is about the best I have experienced, as are the complimentary robes. By the way, there is no additional charge to use the gym, sauna or steam room. The rooms are really beautiful and relatively spacious with spectacular interior decorating, bathrooms, showers, etc.Overall, I would give four stars because of the beautiful rooms, excellent employees, and very luxurious steam room, sauna, and shower facilities. 
